Odaily Planet Daily News Fox Business reporter Eleanor Terrett wrote on the X platform that according to multiple legal sources, the SEC has been giving priority to cases with court deadlines, which explains why no suspension requests have been seen in the Ripple and Kraken cases: 
The next court deadline for the Ripple case is April 16; 
The deadline for the Kraken case appears to be March 31; 
The Binance case has been put on hold until April 14; 
The deadline for the Lejilex case is April 11; 
Coinbase and the SEC have agreed to extend the deadline, allowing the SEC to respond to Coinbase's interlocutory appeal application by March 14. 
It is reported that the Cryptocurrency Task Force, Congress, and the Presidential Working Group on Digital Assets may be working to fill the regulatory gap that led to these lawsuits being filed in the first place.
